<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<text id="02-output-contract" title="Web Scraping Element Extraction Output Contract" version="1.0.0" est_tokens="800" depth="essential">
  <summary>JSON Schema for the per-row extraction artefact emitted by the extractor module. A row that doesn't validate is written to the invalid side-stream, not the main JSONL.</summary>

  <section title="JSON Schema (draft-07)">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "$id": "https://faion.net/schemas/web-scraping-element-extraction.json",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["artefact_id", "source", "row_index", "fields", "normalizers_applied", "version", "last_reviewed"],
  "properties": {
    "artefact_id": {"type": "string", "pattern": "^wsx-[a-z0-9-]{6,}$"},
    "source":      {"type": "string", "minLength": 1},
    "row_index":   {"type": "integer", "minimum": 0},
    "fields":      {"type": "object", "additionalProperties": {"type": ["string", "number", "integer", "boolean", "null"]}},
    "normalizers_applied": {
      "type": "array",
      "minItems": 1,
      "items": {"enum": ["text-trim", "text-collapse-ws", "text-strip-nonprintable", "price-to-float", "date-to-iso", "table-shape-check"]}
    },
    "parse_failures": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["field", "reason"],
        "properties": {"field": {"type": "string"}, "reason": {"type": "string"}}
      }
    },
    "verdict":      {"enum": ["approve", "block-no-normalizer", "block-wrong-api"]},
    "version":      {"type": "string", "pattern": "^\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+$"},
    "last_reviewed":{"type": "string", "format": "date"}
  }
}
]]></code>
  </section>

  <example valid="true">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "artefact_id": "wsx-news-row-0042",
  "source": "example.com/news",
  "row_index": 42,
  "fields": {"title": "Migration to Go shadow router", "price": null, "published_at": "2026-05-20"},
  "normalizers_applied": ["text-trim", "text-collapse-ws", "date-to-iso"],
  "parse_failures": [],
  "verdict": "approve",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "last_reviewed": "2026-05-23"
}
]]></code>
  </example>

  <example valid="false">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "artefact_id": "row0042",
  "source": "example.com/news",
  "row_index": 42,
  "fields": {"title": "  Migration to Go shadow router\n\n ", "price": "$1,234.56"},
  "normalizers_applied": [],
  "verdict": "approve",
  "version": "1.0",
  "last_reviewed": "today"
}
]]></code>
    <note>artefact_id missing wsx- prefix; title has un-normalized whitespace; price kept as raw string (no price-to-float); normalizers_applied empty (violates r3); verdict=approve impossible without normalizers; version + last_reviewed malformed.</note>
  </example>

  <section title="Forbidden patterns">
    <antipattern>
      <description>verdict=approve with normalizers_applied empty.</description>
      <reason>Violates r3 — normalization is mandatory at extraction time.</reason>
    </antipattern>
    <antipattern>
      <description>fields contain raw price strings ("$1,234.56") with no parse_failures entry.</description>
      <reason>Either price-to-float succeeded (return float) or it failed (entry in parse_failures + null in field). Raw string surviving is silent corruption.</reason>
    </antipattern>
    <antipattern>
      <description>$eval used against a multi-element selector returning an array.</description>
      <reason>$eval is single-element only; silently drops all but the first match.</reason>
    </antipattern>
  </section>

  <reference path="templates/web-scraping-element-extraction.json">Schema canonical location.</reference>
  <reference path="scripts/validate-web-scraping-element-extraction.py">Validator that enforces this contract.</reference>
</text>
